attributes.name: data-umami-event
attributes.value: Clicks FAQ 2 - why try GJ

default.123abaa0-4e04-4882-ac91-ffbb5cb32d1a:
Here are three reasons (we have more!).
  1. First. Gapjunction allows you to run your integrations anywhere you want - your local PC, a Raspberry Pi, your private cloud, or our secure cloud (built on Google's infrastructure), you decide!
  2. Second. Connect Hardware + Software. Gapjunction is the only complete middleware. Whether you interface with instruments to automate data capture, or link 9 applications together in a single workflow, Gapjunction is the only solution today that covers all sides! No more Instrument Manager + Corepoint + Zapier. Just Gapjunction
  3. Third. Simple great pricing! Gapjunction is billed based on the number of channels you run. The end. We don't dime and nickel the number of messages, bandwidth use or paywall features, never. Simple metric, excellent for planning your costs
default.8be45b5c-f1c5-4edb-af01-afec95d44fec: What is unique about Gapjunction, why should we try it?

attributes.name: data-umami-event
attributes.value: Clicks FAQ 7 - GJ vs traditional engines

default.123abaa0-4e04-4882-ac91-ffbb5cb32d1a: Yes; and we believe you should try it out. Traditional integration engines (e.g. Mirth Connect, Cloverleaf, Iguana, Corepoint, PilotFish etc.) are amazing tools, but their biggest flaws are that they have a steep learning curve, are very expensive, and require IT teams. With the sheer volume of healthcare data being generated, and the advances in AI, data integration is a must-have for every healthcare business no matter how small, and traditional integration engines fail at this - they don't serve small establishments. This is the perfect place to replace them with Gapjunction. If you are a health business that wants an integration engine that just works, that your colleagues can use themselves without waiting for IT, then Gapjunction it is!
default.8be45b5c-f1c5-4edb-af01-afec95d44fec: Can Gapjunction replace traditional integration engines like Corepoint, Mirth Connect?

attributes.name: data-umami-event
attributes.value: Clicks get access from why Gapjunction?

default.31a09482-0ef3-4d4e-892c-262bc15e3f14: Create complex automations, capture and transform data in various formats (e.g. HL7 <> JSON) without writing any code
One-click deployment of integrations to any environment you control - local PC, mobile phone, on-prem server or cloud
Gapjunction currently powers 22,000+ flows every week for organizations like yours, and can scale to millions
Connect hardware (e.g. POCT Devices, Microscopes, Scales, Printers) and applications (e.g. EHRs, LIMS, ELNs, CRMs, third-party apps) in one single engine

_ww-text_text.en: Streamline data exchange across labs, trial sites, and sponsors with a no-code integration engine. Improve protocol adherence, automate reporting, and ensure regulatory-ready data integrity throughout clinical research workflows.

Seamlessly connect analyzers, LIMS, and reporting tools in one no-code engine. Automate sample data transfers, QC checks, and results reporting to save hours, eliminate transcription errors, and scale your lab operations securely.

default.b1fd60ee-5c54-4b3e-b7b8-cec085e06436: Customizable data tables, graphs and dashboards

_ww-text_text.en: Save up to 30 hours/week by securely linking your apps, diagnostic equipment, microscopes & printers via drag-and-drop in our HIPAA-compliant engine

default.edd0e708-8b9a-4d32-9cce-ee4eeac03c73: In Gapjunction, workflows are called "Channels", and every channel begins with a trigger (an event that kicks off the flow of data)
Within a channel you can branch the flow of data based on some logic or perform custom actions and data transformations
A single channel can then perform one or more actions such as storing data, fetching more data, sending commands to hardware or other apps

30c644c5-0d28-4310-a22d-5595f562973c.name: Accordions Utilize the Power of InventoAI

attributes.name: data-umami-event
attributes.value: Clicks FAQ 1 - what is GJ

default.123abaa0-4e04-4882-ac91-ffbb5cb32d1a: Gapjunction is a data integration engine. Think of it as the glue that connects all of your data sources and workflows together across offline, online, hardware and software sources. It connects your hardware (e.g. printers, point-of-care devices, diagnostic equipment, scanners, microscopes etc.), and your software (e.g. EHRs, CRMs, LIMS, Calendars, PACS etc.) ensuring you can integrate data, automate workflows across these different data sources, and securely share data with patients and partners.

attributes.name: data-umami-event
attributes.value: Clicks FAQ 3 - Is GJ technical?

default.123abaa0-4e04-4882-ac91-ffbb5cb32d1a: No, Gapjunction is designed to be user-friendly and accessible, even for those without technical expertise. The platform's intuitive interface makes it easy to setup channels, automate tasks, transform data, and generate insights without coding or advanced technical knowledge.
default.8be45b5c-f1c5-4edb-af01-afec95d44fec: Do I need any technical skills to use Gapjunction?

attributes.name: data-umami-event
attributes.value: Clicks FAQ 5 - Can GJ scale?

default.123abaa0-4e04-4882-ac91-ffbb5cb32d1a: Absolutely. Gapjunction is built to scale with your business, whether you're managing a single channel or hundreds of channels across multiple locations. Its robust architectue ensures that your channels run uninterrupted, up-to-date, and optimized, no matter the size of your operation. As at today, gapjunction runs 20,000+ messages every week for health businesses like you
default.8be45b5c-f1c5-4edb-af01-afec95d44fec: Can Gapjunction handle large-scale data volumes?

attributes.name: data-umami-event
attributes.value: Clicks FAQ 6 - GJ vs Zapier

default.123abaa0-4e04-4882-ac91-ffbb5cb32d1a: First, Zapier is not HIPAA-compliant, meaning you cannot use it to manage patient health information. Second, Gapjunction works offline, can link to your hardware, and can be deployed anywhere you see fit (mobile, local PC, cloud), Zapier cannot do any of that.

attributes.value: Clicks FAQ 8 - is GJ secure?

default.123abaa0-4e04-4882-ac91-ffbb5cb32d1a: Yes; and you decide. Gapjunction is secure, all patient data is encrypted at-rest and in-transit, but more importantly Gapjunction helps you maintain that security by emphasizing secure defaults. Data storage location is completely up to you, because Gapjunction can be deployed anywhere, you may run your channels locally on your PC so the data is only available on your local PC, or you may run them in our secure cloud in many instances. You decide based on the particular workflow and deploy in one-click. This flexibility makes satisfying data residency laws like the GDPR a breeze. Your patients' data never goes anywhere you don't want it to.
